      <h1 class="tg-hero__title">The Holy Catholic Church</h1>
      <p class="tg-hero__intro">
        What did Christ intend when he said "I will build my church"? This study traces the
        Church from its Old Testament foundations through Christ's institution, the apostolic
        pattern, the Ecumenical Councils, the great schisms, the Reformation, and into the
        modern landscape — asking at every stage what a truly biblical, obedient assembly
        looks like and what faithful Christians are called to do.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="tg-hero__key-verse">
        <p>And I tell you, you are Peter, and on this rock I will build my church,
           and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.</p>
        <cite><a class="ref" data-ref="Matthew 16:18">Matthew 16:18</a></cite>
      </blockquote>
